<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Daisy May Cooper paid tribute to her late co-star Michael Sleggs when naming her newborn. </p>

<p>The This Country star, 34, welcomed a baby boy on September 1 but remained in hospital for a 'traumatic few days' after suffering complications in labour. </p>

<p>In a sweet Instagram post on Friday, the actress revealed all was now well as she announced the name of her little one. </p>

<p>Tribute: In a sweet Instagram post on Friday, Daisy May Cooper revealed all was now well with herself and newborn as she paid tribute to her late co-star Michael Sleggs with his name</p>

<p>Alongside a picture of the newborn, she penned: 'Lots of you have been asking what the bubbas name is. We have named him Jack Michael weston.</p>

<p>'The middle name Michael after our dear friend Michael sleggs who we lost last year. May the spirit of sluggs live on! ❤️❤️❤️❤️ <?php echo e('@'); ?>willwestonlandscape [sic]'. </p>

<p>Michael died in July 2019 of heart failure at the age of just 33.</p>

<p>Co-stars: Daisy and her brother Charlie (left) starred alongside Michael Sleggs (right) on the BAFTA-winning BBC Three sitcom, This Country</p>

<p>Just a couple of months prior, in May, Michael revealed he was terminally ill following a 'fairly rapid' deterioration, later clarifying he was suffering from heart failure. </p>

<p>He had played Michael 'Slugs' Slugette on the BBC Three sitcom This Country alongside Daisy, who plays Kerry Mucklowe.    </p>

<p>The show follows the daily exploits of best friends Kerry and Kurtan in rural England.</p>

<p>Tragic loss: Michael died in July 2019 of heart failure at the age of just 33. He had played Michael 'Slugs' Slugette on the BBC Three sitcom</p>

<p>Daisy shares her two-week-old son Michael with husband Will Weston. The couple also have a daughter named Pip. </p>

<p>Last week, the actress revealed she had to stay in hospital for a few days as she penned: 'Cannot thank <?php echo e('@'); ?>deliverysuitegrh for all they are doing for our little bubba and me.</p>

<p>'Its been quite a traumatic few days and they have gone above and beyond' (sic). </p>

<p>Adorable: Daisy shares her two-week-old son Michael with husband Will Weston. The couple also have a daughter named Pip</p>
